Fall 2016

American Politics

Ran through the basics of how the American Government works. I found I already knew most of the material, but it proved to be an interesting course nevertheless.ss

Calculus 2

I learned everything in this class very thoroughly. I mastered advanced integration techniques, and learned how to test for convergence and divergence in a series. In my opinion, this is the least important calculus.

How the internet works

This class gave me a very good idea of how the internet operates. I learned a little bit of everything, from Telnet to HTML and CSS

Intro to Computer Science Part 1

A very basic course on CS taught in Java. We learned the basic structure of a programming language, a few data-structures, and some fundamentals of object-oriented programming.
